      <chapter eId="chp_35">
        <num>35</num>
        <heading>Revenue</heading>
        <article eId="chp_35__art_140">
          <num>35 ILCS 140/</num>
          <heading>Home Rule Cigarette Tax Restriction Act</heading>
          <section eId="sec_35-140-1">
            <num>1</num>
            <heading>If any home rule unit imposes a tax based upon the selling
price of cigarettes, such selling price shall, on and after December 1,
1985, include the charges which are added to prices by sellers on account
of the seller's liability under the Cigarette Tax Act, on account of the
seller's duty to collect from the purchaser the tax imposed under the
Cigarette Use Tax Act, and on account of the seller's duty to collect from
the purchaser any cigarette tax imposed by a home rule unit</heading>
            <subsection eId="sec_35-140-1__subsec_g">
              <num>(g)</num>
              <content>
                <p>of Section 6 of Article VII of the Illinois
Constitution, this Section limits the taxing power of home rule units.</p>
              </content>
            </subsection>
            <authorialNote marker="source">
              <p>Source: P.A. 84-1027.</p>
            </authorialNote>
          </section>
        </article>
